IF YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

721
00:53:46,185 --> 00:53:47,144
I WON'T.

722
00:53:47,186 --> 00:53:49,646
DON'T YOU SAY
ANYTHING EITHER.

723
00:53:49,688 --> 00:53:52,649
JUST GIVE ME
A MINUTE TO SNEAK INSIDE,

724
00:53:52,691 --> 00:54:50,666
AND NO ONE
WILL BE THE WISER.

725
00:54:50,701 --> 00:54:52,668
OH, HELLO, ROGERS.

726
00:54:52,709 --> 00:54:54,670
YOU'RE EARLY
FOR A CHANGE.

727
00:54:54,711 --> 00:54:55,671
CHARLES.

728
00:54:55,712 --> 00:54:58,674
CHARLES VANDERVENTER.

729
00:54:58,715 --> 00:55:00,175
HERE YOU ARE.

730
00:55:00,210 --> 00:55:06,682
RUN ALONG
WITH ROGERS NOW.

731
00:55:06,723 --> 00:55:09,184
IS...THAT ROGERS?

732
00:55:09,219 --> 00:55:10,686
IS IT?
MY GOODNESS.

733
00:55:10,721 --> 00:55:18,694
AND WHO ELSE
WOULD IT BE?

734
00:55:18,735 --> 00:55:19,695
ROGERS!

735
00:55:19,730 --> 00:55:20,696
ROGERS!

736
00:55:20,731 --> 00:55:23,699
CHARLES HAS HAD
A PRETTY TRYING DAY.

737
00:55:23,740 --> 00:55:25,200
PLEASE TELL
MRS. VANDERVENTER

738
00:55:25,242 --> 00:55:58,233
THAT I SUGGEST HE
STAY HOME NEXT WEEK.

739
00:55:58,275 --> 00:56:20,756
HEY!

740
00:56:20,791 --> 00:56:22,758
JUST RELAX,
CHARLIE BOY.

741
00:56:22,799 --> 00:56:25,260
JUST BE REAL NICE
AND QUIET,

742
00:56:25,302 --> 00:56:27,763
AND EVERYTHING
WILL BE ALL RIGHT.

743
00:56:27,804 --> 00:56:29,765
DON'T HURT ME, MISTER.

744
00:56:29,800 --> 00:57:38,834
I WON'T, AND NO ONE
ELSE WILL EITHER.

745
00:57:38,876 --> 00:57:41,336
...AS CROWDS
OF ONLOOKERS

746
00:57:41,371 --> 00:57:43,338
GATHERED TO WATCH THE
POLICE PROCEEDINGS.

747
00:57:43,380 --> 00:57:46,341
NO LEADS HAVE
BEEN UNCOVERED AS OF THIS TIME.

748
00:57:46,383 --> 00:57:48,844
THE ONE PERSON
WHO MIGHT BE ABLE

749
00:57:48,886 --> 00:57:51,346
TO GIVE A DETAILED
DESCRIPTION OF THE KIDNAPPER

750
00:57:51,381 --> 00:57:53,348
REMAINS UNCONSCIOUS
IN INTENSIVE CARE.

751
00:57:53,390 --> 00:58:04,860
[TURNS OFF RADIO]

752
00:58:04,902 --> 00:58:06,361
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

753
00:58:06,403 --> 00:58:08,864
I DIDN'T SURPRISE YOU,
DID I?

754
00:58:08,906 --> 00:58:10,365
SURPRISE US?

755
00:58:10,400 --> 00:58:12,868
SURPRISE US!

756
00:58:12,910 --> 00:58:16,872
OH, COLLIE, WHY IN THE WORLD
DID YOU DO IT?

757
00:58:16,914 --> 00:58:17,873
WHY NOT?

758
00:58:17,915 --> 00:58:19,374
IT'S WHAT
WE PLANNED ON,

759
00:58:19,409 --> 00:58:21,376
WHAT I WAS
SUPPOSED TO DO.

760
00:58:21,411 --> 00:58:23,879
NOT AFTER YOU MADE
A MISTAKE AND...

761
00:58:23,921 --> 00:58:26,381
I GOT TO HAND IT TO YOU.

762
00:58:26,423 --> 00:58:28,884
I DON'T KNOW ANOTHER GUY
IN THIS COUNTRY...

763
00:58:28,926 --> 00:58:32,387
PULLS A STUNT LIKE THAT
AND GETS AWAY WITH IT.

764
00:58:32,429 --> 00:58:34,389
OH, UNCLE BUD,
SURE, THERE IS.

765
00:58:34,431 --> 00:58:37,392
JUST PICK YOURSELF
A GUY WHO'S A LITTLE BIT OFF

766
00:58:37,434 --> 00:58:39,394
AND THROW HIM A CURVE.

767
00:58:39,429 --> 00:58:43,899
YOU HOLD THE SHORT END
OF THAT STICK JUST SO LONG,

768
00:58:43,941 --> 00:58:46,401
AND THEN YOU'RE GOING
TO START SWINGING IT.

769
00:58:46,443 --> 00:58:47,402
SHUT UP.

770
00:58:47,444 --> 00:58:48,403
WHAT?

771
00:58:48,445 --> 00:58:49,905
I SAID SHUT UP.

772
00:58:49,940 --> 00:58:52,407
WHAT'S THIS
"CURVE" STUFF?

773
00:58:52,449 --> 00:58:54,910
WHO'S THROWING
WHO A CURVE?

774
00:58:54,952 --> 00:58:56,411
HUH?

775
00:58:56,453 --> 00:58:58,413
HOW ABOUT IT?

776
00:58:58,455 --> 00:59:01,416
YOU WERE SET TO USE
THAT GUN AN HOUR AGO,

777
00:59:01,451 --> 00:59:04,419
SO WHY DON'T YOU
USE IT NOW?

778
00:59:04,461 --> 00:59:14,930
CAN'T YOU MAKE UP
YOUR MIND?

779
00:59:14,972 --> 00:59:17,432
YOU'RE SCARED.

780
00:59:17,474 --> 00:59:19,935
STUPID AND SCARED.

781
00:59:19,970 --> 00:59:21,436
LET ME HELP YOU.

782
00:59:21,471 --> 00:59:25,941
STOP IT!

783
00:59:25,983 --> 00:59:29,444
I JUST WANT TO KNOW WHAT
THIS IS ALL ABOUT.

784
00:59:29,479 --> 00:59:30,445
NO.

785
00:59:30,480 --> 00:59:33,448
I TOLD YOU, FAY,
RIGHT FROM THE BEGINNING,

786
00:59:33,490 --> 00:59:34,950
THAT I WASN'T STUPID,

787
00:59:34,992 --> 00:59:38,954
AND I DIDN'T LIKE FOR PEOPLE
TO TREAT ME LIKE I WAS.

788
00:59:38,996 --> 00:59:42,457
WHAT'S THAT
GOT TO DO WITH IT?

789
00:59:42,492 --> 00:59:44,459
DOES IT HAVE SOMETHING TO DO
WITH YESTERDAY?

790
00:59:44,501 --> 00:59:47,462
LOOK, I'M REALLY
SORRY ABOUT THAT, DARLING,

791
00:59:47,504 --> 00:59:50,465
BUT IT CAME AS SUCH
A SHOCK TO ME.

792
00:59:50,500 --> 00:59:52,968
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS DOING.

793
00:59:53,010 --> 00:59:54,469
I RAN OFF AND
STARTED DRINKING

794
00:59:54,511 --> 00:59:57,472
AND MADE SUCH
A MESS OF MYSELF

795
00:59:57,514 --> 01:00:00,476
THAT I WAS ASHAMED
TO FACE YOU.

796
01:00:00,511 --> 01:00:01,477
FORGET IT.

797
01:00:01,512 --> 01:00:03,979
I KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT YOU FELT.

798
01:00:04,021 --> 01:00:04,980
THEN IS IT
ABOUT TODAY?

799
01:00:05,022 --> 01:00:07,983
I WANTED TO BE
IN THE CAR WITH YOU,

800
01:00:08,025 --> 01:00:09,485
BUT THE WAY
I WAS FEELING,

801
01:00:09,520 --> 01:00:11,487
I WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN MUCH HELP.

802
01:00:11,522 --> 01:00:15,491
BUT YOU FELT GOOD ENOUGH
TO RIDE WITH UNCLE BUD.

803
01:00:15,532 --> 01:00:16,492
CONVENIENTLY SHOW UP.

804
01:00:16,533 --> 01:00:17,993
I STILL FELT SICK,

805
01:00:18,035 --> 01:00:20,996
BUT I WAS WORRIED
ABOUT LEAVING YOU TO DO EVERYTHING.

806
01:00:21,031 --> 01:00:25,000
THAT'S JUST THE WAY
IT WAS, KID.

807
01:00:25,042 --> 01:00:28,003
IF WE WEREN'T THERE,
YOU WOULD'VE TAKEN THE WRONG BOY.

808
01:00:28,045 --> 01:00:29,505
HASN'T IT
OCCURRED TO YOU

809
01:00:29,540 --> 01:00:35,093
THAT MAYBE I PICKED UP
THE WRONG KID ON PURPOSE?

810
01:00:35,135 --> 01:00:39,014
WHAT?

811
01:00:39,056 --> 01:00:41,016
I AM GETTING FED UP.

812
01:00:41,051 --> 01:00:44,520
WHAT THE HELL
IS HE TALKING ABOUT?

813
01:00:44,561 --> 01:00:48,524
THE KID'S JUST GOT
THE WRONG SLANT ON THINGS.

814
01:00:48,565 --> 01:00:49,525
OH, DO I?

815
01:00:49,560 --> 01:00:50,526
DOES HE?

816
01:00:50,561 --> 01:00:54,029
YEAH. DON'T YOU
REMEMBER THE OTHER DAY?

817
01:00:54,071 --> 01:00:57,032
WE TALKED ALL ABOUT IT,
YOU REMEMBER,

818
01:00:57,074 --> 01:01:01,036
ABOUT WE WOULDN'T ACTUALLY
GO THROUGH WITH THE JOB.

819
01:01:01,071 --> 01:01:06,041
I'D STEP IN AT THE LAST MINUTE
AND BE THE BIG HERO

820
01:01:06,083 --> 01:01:08,544
AND COLLECT THE REWARD,
ET CETERA.

821
01:01:08,585 --> 01:01:10,546
BUT IT
COULDN'T BE DONE.

822
01:01:10,581 --> 01:01:19,054
SOMEONE WOULD HAVE
TO GET CAUGHT OR--

823
01:01:19,096 --> 01:01:23,058
SO THAT'S
WHAT YOU THINK?

824
01:01:23,100 --> 01:01:25,561
THAT'S WHAT
YOU THINK OF ME?

825
01:01:25,602 --> 01:01:29,064
WHY NOT?

826
01:01:29,106 --> 01:01:31,567
WELL, SURE.
WHY NOT?

827
01:01:31,602 --> 01:01:33,569
IF A PERSON WON'T STOP
AT KIDNAPPING,

828
01:01:33,610 --> 01:01:35,571
WHY SHOULD SHE
STOP AT MURDER?

829
01:01:35,612 --> 01:01:36,572
FAY.

830
01:01:36,613 --> 01:01:39,074
BECAUSE PEOPLE WHO'VE
BECOME WHAT WE HAVE,

831
01:01:39,116 --> 01:01:42,578
WE WERE BOUND
TO ARRIVE AT IT SOONER OR LATER.

832
01:01:42,613 --> 01:01:45,581
YOU ARE DAMN WRONG
ABOUT NOT BEING STUPID.

833
01:01:45,622 --> 01:01:49,585
YOU ARE, I AM, AND UNCLE BUD DECIDED--
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

834
01:01:49,620 --> 01:01:58,594
YOU KNOW, UH, WE SHOULD REALLY STOP
THIS MOPING AROUND.

835
01:01:58,635 --> 01:02:02,097
LOOK, WE HAD A LITTLE
MISUNDERSTANDING.

836
01:02:02,132 --> 01:02:04,391
AND IT'S ALL OVER NOW.

837
01:02:04,433 --> 01:02:07,394
WE GOT WHAT WE WANTED.

838
01:02:07,436 --> 01:02:10,898
WE ARE ABOUT TO COLLECT.

839
01:02:10,939 --> 01:02:12,399
YES, GENTLEMEN AND LADY,

840
01:02:12,441 --> 01:02:15,903
NOW WE CAN COLLECT.

841
01:02:15,944 --> 01:02:21,909
WELL, THAT'S
JUST WHAT I SAID.

842
01:02:21,950 --> 01:02:24,411
I GOT AN IDEA, KID.

843
01:02:24,453 --> 01:02:26,413
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

844
01:02:26,455 --> 01:02:28,415
IF IT'S OK WITH YOU,

845
01:02:28,457 --> 01:02:31,418
THE FIRST THING
I OUGHT TO DO IS THE CAR.

846
01:02:31,460 --> 01:02:34,421
I CAN HAVE IT SCRAPPED IN ONE HOUR.

847
01:02:34,463 --> 01:02:35,923
IN THE MEANTIME,

848
01:02:35,964 --> 01:02:37,424
I SEND
THE RANSOM NOTE.

849
01:02:37,466 --> 01:02:40,427
LOOK, WE'VE BEEN
THROUGH ALL THIS.

850
01:02:40,469 --> 01:02:42,930
I JUST DON'T
WANT YOU TO GET

851
01:02:42,971 --> 01:02:44,431
ANY MORE
WRONG IDEAS.

852
01:02:44,473 --> 01:02:48,936
DON'T GIVE ME
ANY REASONS, AND I WON'T.

853
01:02:48,977 --> 01:04:22,029
OK.

854
01:04:22,070 --> 01:04:25,032
DID HE
EAT ALL RIGHT?

855
01:04:25,073 --> 01:04:28,035
DON'T TELL ME
YOU DON'T KNOW.

856
01:04:28,076 --> 01:04:30,537
HE MUST HAVE
BEEN PRETTY HUNGRY.

857
01:04:30,579 --> 01:04:32,039
IT HADN'T
OCCURRED TO ME.

858
01:04:32,080 --> 01:04:34,541
I SEE NOW THAT
HE MUST HAVE BEEN.

859
01:04:34,583 --> 01:04:36,543
I'VE BEEN
THINKING THINGS OVER.

860
01:04:36,585 --> 01:04:40,047
I THINK MAYBE I
WAS WRONG ABOUT TODAY.

861
01:04:40,088 --> 01:04:41,548
YOU THINK SO?

862
01:04:41,590 --> 01:04:42,549
MAYBE?

863
01:04:42,591 --> 01:04:45,052
ABOUT YOU,
NOT ABOUT UNCLE BUD.

864
01:04:45,093 --> 01:04:48,055
I KNOW WHAT
HE PLANNED ON DOING.

865
01:04:48,096 --> 01:04:52,559
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU HAD TO BE IN ON IT.

866
01:04:52,601 --> 01:04:53,560
WELL...

867
01:04:53,602 --> 01:04:54,561
I MIGHT NOT HAVE.

868
01:04:54,603 --> 01:04:56,063
I MAYBE DIDN'T.

869
01:04:56,104 --> 01:04:57,564
IT'S ALGEBRA,
ISN'T IT?

870
01:04:57,606 --> 01:05:00,067
TWO MINUSES
GIVE YOU A PLUS.

871
01:05:00,108 --> 01:05:02,569
LOOK.

872
01:05:02,611 --> 01:05:04,571
DID YOU
OR DIDN'T YOU?

873
01:05:04,613 --> 01:05:06,073
JUST TELL ME.

874
01:05:06,114 --> 01:05:10,077
IF YOU HAVE TO ASK
FOR THE ANSWER, IT DOESN'T COUNT.

875
01:05:10,118 --> 01:05:12,579
WELL, THEN YOU
TELL ME THIS.

876
01:05:12,621 --> 01:05:15,082
ABOUT YOU FINDING
OUT ABOUT ME,

877
01:05:15,123 --> 01:05:19,086
WOULD THAT HAVE
BEEN ALL RIGHT?

878
01:05:19,127 --> 01:05:21,588
BEFORE THIS AFTERNOON, I COULD
HAVE ANSWERED YOU,

879
01:05:21,630 --> 01:05:24,091
AND YOU WOULD
HAVE BELIEVED ME.

880
01:05:24,132 --> 01:05:26,593
BUT AFTER YOUR
FLAT ACCUSATION...

881
01:05:26,635 --> 01:05:28,595
ALL RIGHT!

882
01:05:28,637 --> 01:05:37,104
WHY DO YOU
HARP ON THAT?

883
01:05:37,146 --> 01:05:41,608
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE THOUGHT
IF YOU WERE IN MY PLACE?

884
01:05:41,650 --> 01:06:10,137
EXACTLY WHAT
YOU DID, MY FRIEND.

885
01:06:10,179 --> 01:06:13,640
THAT DOOR
LEADS TO A WALK.

886
01:06:13,682 --> 01:06:16,643
AT THE END OF THE WALK,
THERE'S A LANE.

887
01:06:16,685 --> 01:06:20,147
AT THE END OF THE LANE,
THERE'S A HIGHWAY.

888
01:06:20,189 --> 01:06:23,650
THIS DOOR'S WIDE ENOUGH
FOR TWO PEOPLE.

889
01:06:23,692 --> 01:06:28,655
THESE TWO?

890
01:06:28,697 --> 01:06:32,159
WE COULD END
ALL THIS RIGHT NOW.

891
01:06:32,201 --> 01:06:35,162
YOU AND ME.

892
01:06:35,204 --> 01:06:38,665
THEN WHAT?

893
01:06:38,707 --> 01:06:41,668
THEN WE FIGURE
IT OUT TOGETHER.

894
01:06:41,710 --> 01:06:46,673
YOU AND ME,
TOGETHER FOREVER?

895
01:06:46,715 --> 01:06:48,675
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
THAT, COLLIE?

896
01:06:48,717 --> 01:06:52,679
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
THERE COULD BE A YOU AND ME?

897
01:06:52,721 --> 01:06:55,682
I KNOW IT, FAY.

898
01:06:55,724 --> 01:07:00,187
COLLIE AND FAY.

899
01:07:00,229 --> 01:07:03,690
THROUGH THAT DOOR,
DOWN THE LANE...

900
01:07:03,732 --> 01:07:12,199
ONTO THE HIGHWAY.

901
01:07:12,241 --> 01:07:14,201
WE COULD DO IT, FAY.

902
01:07:14,243 --> 01:07:41,728
I CAN TAKE CARE
OF YOU REAL GOOD.

903
01:07:41,770 --> 01:07:45,232
OH, I ALMOST FORGOT.
THE CAR KEYS, COLLIE.

904
01:07:45,274 --> 01:07:46,733
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

905
01:07:46,775 --> 01:07:47,734
IT'S RATHER SIMPLE.

906
01:07:47,776 --> 01:07:49,736
I WANT THE KEYS
TO THE CAR.

907
01:07:49,778 --> 01:07:53,740
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

908
01:07:53,782 --> 01:08:34,281
WHY, I'M GOING OUT.

909
01:08:34,323 --> 01:08:36,283
MAYBE THIS WAS HER PLAN,

910
01:08:36,325 --> 01:08:39,786
A WAY OF CUTTING ME
OUT OF THE DEAL.

911
01:08:39,828 --> 01:08:41,788
SHE'D POINT ME
IN ONE DIRECTION

912
01:08:41,830 --> 01:08:44,291
SO SHE COULD
MOVE IN ANOTHER.

913
01:08:44,333 --> 01:08:45,792
RIGHT FROM THE BEGINNING,

914
01:08:45,834 --> 01:08:47,794
SHE'D BEEN ABLE
TO GET ME SO MIXED UP

915
01:08:47,836 --> 01:08:50,297
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS DOING.

916
01:08:50,339 --> 01:08:52,799
SHE SENT ME AWAY
THAT FIRST TIME,

917
01:08:52,841 --> 01:08:54,301
BUT SHE KNEW
I'D COME BACK.

918
01:08:54,343 --> 01:08:56,803
I DIDN'T HAVE ANYPLACE
ELSE TO GO AND--

919
01:08:56,845 --> 01:08:57,805
MISTER?

920
01:08:57,846 --> 01:08:58,806
MISTER.

921
01:08:58,847 --> 01:08:59,807
I'M SICK.

922
01:08:59,848 --> 01:09:05,312
I THINK
I'M GOING TO--

923
01:09:05,354 --> 01:09:07,815
SORRY. I'LL CLEAN
IT UP, MISTER.

924
01:09:07,856 --> 01:09:09,316
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THAT.

925
01:09:09,358 --> 01:09:12,820
JUST CUT LOOSE
AS MUCH AS YOU WANT TO.

926
01:09:12,861 --> 01:09:15,322
YOU'RE--YOU'RE
NOT MAD AT ME?

927
01:09:15,364 --> 01:09:18,826
WHY WOULD I BE MAD
AT A LITTLE BOY

928
01:09:18,867 --> 01:09:20,327
FOR BEING SICK?

929
01:09:20,369 --> 01:09:23,330
HONEST, YOU'RE
NOT MAD AT ME?

930
01:09:23,372 --> 01:09:25,332
NO, I'M NOT MAD.

931
01:09:25,374 --> 01:09:28,335
NO ONE ELSE
IS GOING TO BE MAD EITHER,

932
01:09:28,377 --> 01:09:35,843
BECAUSE IF
THEY DO GET MAD...

933
01:09:35,884 --> 01:09:41,348
THEY JUST BETTER
NOT. THAT'S ALL.

934
01:09:41,390 --> 01:09:43,350
I LIKE YOU, MISTER.

935
01:09:43,392 --> 01:09:47,855
I LIKE YOU VERY MUCH.

936
01:09:47,896 --> 01:09:50,858
COLLIE, WAKE UP.

937
01:09:50,899 --> 01:09:52,860
WAKE UP, COLLIE.

938
01:09:52,901 --> 01:09:53,861
AAH!

939
01:09:53,902 --> 01:09:55,362
PUT THE GUN DOWN!

940
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:58,365
IT'S THE BOY, COLLIE.
HE'S...

941
01:09:58,407 --> 01:10:00,367
WHAT DID YOU
DO TO HIM?

942
01:10:00,409 --> 01:10:01,869
DO TO HIM?

943
01:10:01,910 --> 01:10:03,370
HE'S SICK, THAT'S WHAT.

944
01:10:03,412 --> 01:10:24,391
HE LOOKS
LIKE HE'S DYING.

945
01:10:24,433 --> 01:10:25,893
DAMN IT,
SAY SOMETHING.

946
01:10:25,934 --> 01:10:26,894
DO SOMETHING.

947
01:10:26,935 --> 01:10:28,395
TURN ON THE RADIO.

948
01:10:28,437 --> 01:10:29,897
TURN ON
THE RADIO?

949
01:10:29,938 --> 01:10:31,398
THERE'S
PROBABLY SOMETHING

950
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:32,900
ABOUT HIS CONDITION
ON THERE.

951
01:10:32,941 --> 01:10:35,402
I THINK
I KNOW WHAT IT IS.

952
01:10:35,444 --> 01:10:37,905
THERE WERE SOME GUYS
IN THE HOSPITAL.

953
01:10:37,946 --> 01:10:45,412
TURN IT ON.

954
01:10:45,454 --> 01:10:48,916
HEY, CHARLIE BOY.

955
01:10:48,957 --> 01:10:59,927
YOU'LL BE OK.

956
01:10:59,968 --> 01:11:01,428
GOOD NEWS, KID.

957
01:11:01,470 --> 01:11:03,931
THE FAMILY'S READY
TO PAY UP.

958
01:11:03,972 --> 01:11:06,934
THEY TOLD THE POLICE
TO STAY OUT.

959
01:11:06,975 --> 01:11:08,435
THEY JUST
WANT THE BOY.

960
01:11:08,477 --> 01:11:09,937
THEY AIN'T GOING
TO BE PICKY

961
01:11:09,978 --> 01:11:11,939
WHETHER HE'S
ALIVE OR NOT?

962
01:11:11,980 --> 01:11:12,940
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

963
01:11:12,981 --> 01:11:14,441
HE'S GOT DIABETES.

964
01:11:14,483 --> 01:11:16,944
IT SAYS SOMETHING
ABOUT THAT IN HERE.

965
01:11:16,985 --> 01:11:19,947
WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT HE'D
HAVE A THING LIKE THAT?

966
01:11:19,988 --> 01:11:22,950
ALL THAT STARCH AND SUGAR
WASN'T GOOD FOR HIM.

967
01:11:22,991 --> 01:11:24,451
WONDER IT
DIDN'T KILL HIM.

968
01:11:24,493 --> 01:11:25,953
MAYBE
IT WILL YET.

969
01:11:25,994 --> 01:11:27,955
MAYBE I'LL GET
HIM NEXT TIME.

970
01:11:27,996 --> 01:11:29,456
SAY WHAT
YOU MEAN.

971
01:11:29,498 --> 01:11:30,958
NOW, NOW.

972
01:11:30,999 --> 01:11:31,959
COME ON.

973
01:11:32,000 --> 01:11:35,462
SO, KID, WHAT
ARE YOU DRINKING?

974
01:11:35,504 --> 01:11:36,964
HE NEEDS INSULIN.

975
01:11:37,005 --> 01:11:40,968
HE'LL DIE IF HE
DOESN'T GET IT.

976
01:11:41,009 --> 01:11:43,470
I KNOW
A COUPLE OF PLACES,

977
01:11:43,512 --> 01:11:47,474
BUT WITH IT BEING
IN ALL THE PAPERS AND EVERYTHING,

978
01:11:47,516 --> 01:11:51,979
IT'S LIKE ADVERTISING
THAT WE HAVE THE BOY.

979
01:11:52,020 --> 01:11:52,980
I SEE YOUR POINT.

980
01:11:53,021 --> 01:11:55,816
BESIDES, IF YOU LOOK AT IT
FROM ONE ANGLE,

981
01:11:55,858 --> 01:11:58,819
IT'D BE LESS RISKY
FOR US IF HE DIED.

982
01:11:58,861 --> 01:12:01,321
WE GET THE MONEY
BEFOREHAND IN ANY CASE.

983
01:12:01,363 --> 01:12:02,823
WITHOUT HIM
AROUND AS EVIDENCE

984
01:12:02,865 --> 01:12:05,826
OR SOMEONE WHO CAN
IDENTIFY US, WELL...

985
01:12:05,868 --> 01:12:08,829
I WOULDN'T WANT THAT NICE
LITTLE BOY TO DIE,

986
01:12:08,871 --> 01:12:10,330
BUT IF WE
COULDN'T HELP IT,

987
01:12:10,372 --> 01:12:14,835
IT'D SURE TURN OUT
NICE FOR US.

988
01:12:14,877 --> 01:12:17,838
I WAS POINTING OUT
HOW YOU'D LOOK AT IT.

989
01:12:17,880 --> 01:12:19,840
I DON'T SEE IT
THAT WAY.

990
01:12:19,882 --> 01:12:22,843
IF THINGS DON'T GO
AS SMOOTH AS WE HOPE,

991
01:12:22,885 --> 01:12:25,345
IT'D SURE BE BETTER
IF HE WAS ALIVE.

992
01:12:25,387 --> 01:12:27,848
ANY WAY YOU LOOK AT IT,
YOU'RE RIGHT,

993
01:12:27,890 --> 01:12:29,349
BUT HOW'S THAT LEAVE US?

994
01:12:29,391 --> 01:12:31,351
GET SOME INSULIN
AT DOC GOLDMAN'S.

995
01:12:31,393 --> 01:12:33,854
YOU GET HIM OUT
ON A FAKE CALL.

996
01:12:33,896 --> 01:12:36,857
I SLIP IN,
GET THE STUFF.

997
01:12:36,899 --> 01:12:42,362
SOUND GOOD
TO YOU, FAY?

998
01:12:42,404 --> 01:12:43,363
NO CAR.

999
01:12:43,405 --> 01:12:46,366
HE MUST HAVE
LEFT ALREADY.

1000
01:12:46,408 --> 01:12:47,868
NOW REMEMBER, KID.

1001
01:12:47,910 --> 01:12:52,372
THE POOL HALL,
THE CORNER OF MAIN AND 5th.

1002
01:12:52,414 --> 01:12:53,874
WE'RE PALS,
RIGHT, KID?

1003
01:12:53,916 --> 01:12:56,376
THAT A BOY, KID.

1004
01:12:56,418 --> 01:14:22,963
YOU'RE DOING FINE.

1005
01:14:23,005 --> 01:14:24,464
YOU CHEATING BASTARD.

1006
01:14:24,506 --> 01:14:27,467
YOU THOUGHT I'D NEVER
CATCH UP WITH YOU?

1007
01:14:27,509 --> 01:14:28,969
WELL, GUESS WHAT?

1008
01:14:29,011 --> 01:14:31,972
I JUST NEED
A LITTLE MORE TIME.

1009
01:14:32,014 --> 01:14:38,979
I'LL GIVE YOU SOMETHING,
YOU SORRY SON OF A BITCH.

1010
01:14:39,021 --> 01:14:41,482
YOU WERE GOING TO
GIVE IT TO ME?

1011
01:14:41,523 --> 01:14:43,484
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

1012
01:14:43,525 --> 01:14:45,486
WHERE'D HE
PICK YOU UP?

1013
01:14:45,527 --> 01:14:48,489
I CAME THROUGH THE DOOR,
AND THERE HE WAS.

1014
01:14:48,530 --> 01:14:50,491
HE COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
FOLLOWING YOU?

1015
01:14:50,532 --> 01:14:52,993
NO, NO. HE WAS JUST
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

1016
01:14:53,035 --> 01:15:27,027
BOY, I WOULD
HATE TO THINK...NO.

1017
01:15:27,069 --> 01:15:30,531
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING. YOU'RE CRAZY.

1018
01:15:30,572 --> 01:15:32,533
BUT I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING,

1019
01:15:32,574 --> 01:16:32,593
AND YOU'RE
THROUGH DOING IT.

1020
01:16:32,634 --> 01:16:38,599
OK, CHARLIE BOY.

1021
01:16:38,640 --> 01:16:49,610
OK.

1022
01:16:49,651 --> 01:16:52,112
YOU CAN GO IN
AND LOOK AT HIM

1023
01:16:52,154 --> 01:16:55,616
IF YOU WANT TO.

1024
01:16:55,657 --> 01:16:57,117
I CAN, HUH?

1025
01:16:57,159 --> 01:17:01,121
HE'S ALL RIGHT,
AND HE'LL STAY THAT WAY.

1026
01:17:01,163 --> 01:17:04,124
HOW LONG'S THIS
STUFF GOING TO LAST?

1027
01:17:04,166 --> 01:17:07,127
LONG ENOUGH TO DECIDE
WHAT TO DO WITH HIM.

1028
01:17:07,169 --> 01:17:08,629
YOU WOULDN'T
BE THINKING

1029
01:17:08,670 --> 01:17:16,637
ABOUT GIVING HIM
BACK FOR FREE, WOULD YOU?

1030
01:17:16,678 --> 01:17:19,139
I DON'T KNOW.

1031
01:17:19,181 --> 01:17:20,641
ARE YOU?

1032
01:17:20,682 --> 01:17:22,643
SKIP IT. I'LL BE
SCREWING MYSELF

1033
01:17:22,684 --> 01:17:24,645
IF I TALK TO YOU
MUCH LONGER.

1034
01:17:24,686 --> 01:17:27,648
I'M GETTING MYSELF
SOMETHING TO EAT NOW.

1035
01:17:27,689 --> 01:17:28,649
POOR COLLIE.

1036
01:17:28,690 --> 01:17:32,653
THEY MAY HANG HIM,
BUT HE'LL FILL HIS STOMACH FIRST.

1037
01:17:32,694 --> 01:17:33,654
WITH FOOD.

1038
01:17:33,695 --> 01:17:35,656
HA. VERY GOOD.

1039
01:17:35,697 --> 01:17:39,159
THAT SORT OF THING
THROWS ME ABOUT YOU, COLLIE.

1040
01:17:39,201 --> 01:17:41,161
YOU'RE SO SHARP
SOMETIMES THAT...

1041
01:17:41,203 --> 01:17:43,163
YEAH?

1042
01:17:43,205 --> 01:17:45,165
NEVER MIND.
THAT'S HOW IT IS.

1043
01:17:45,207 --> 01:17:47,668
FAY, IF I ONLY KNEW
WHAT YOU WANTED...

1044
01:17:47,709 --> 01:17:57,177
IF YOU TALKED STRAIGHT
TO ME, MAYBE I COULD...

1045
01:17:57,219 --> 01:18:04,184
THAT'S A LOT OF IFS
AND MAYBES, MY FRIEND.

1046
01:18:04,226 --> 01:18:07,688
SO MAYBE SOMEDAY...

1047
01:18:07,729 --> 01:22:45,841
IF...

1048
01:22:45,883 --> 01:23:06,862
COLLIE.

1049
01:23:06,904 --> 01:23:10,365
I JUST SPOKE
TO UNCLE BUD.

1050
01:23:10,400 --> 01:23:11,867
YEAH?

1051
01:23:11,902 --> 01:23:15,370
HE THINKS WE SHOULD COME
OVER THERE RIGHT AWAY.

1052
01:23:15,412 --> 01:23:17,873
GO ON.

1053
01:23:17,915 --> 01:23:19,374
WHY DOES UNCLE BUD

1054
01:23:19,409 --> 01:23:24,379
THINK WE SHOULD
GO OVER RIGHT AWAY?

1055
01:23:24,421 --> 01:23:30,886
HONEY.

1056
01:23:30,921 --> 01:23:37,392
YOU'RE NOT AFRAID
TO TELL ME, ARE YOU, FAY?

1057
01:23:37,434 --> 01:23:44,900
AFTER ALL, TWO PEOPLE
AS CLOSE AS US...

1058
01:23:44,942 --> 01:23:47,402
SWEETHEARTS,
I GUESS YOU'D CALL US,

1059
01:23:47,444 --> 01:23:50,405
SHOULDN'T BE AFRAID
OF EACH OTHER.

1060
01:23:50,440 --> 01:23:58,413
IT'S THE BOY, COLLIE.
HE RAN AWAY.

1061
01:23:58,455 --> 01:24:00,916
WELL, HE CAN'T BE
VERY FAR.

1062
01:24:00,951 --> 01:24:02,417
HE'S PROBABLY
HIDING SOMEWHERE.

1063
01:24:02,452 --> 01:24:04,419
I LOOKED BEFORE
I CALLED UNCLE BUD.

1064
01:24:04,461 --> 01:24:07,422
WELL,
WE'LL LOOK TOGETHER.

1065
01:24:07,464 --> 01:24:10,926
THAT WAY, IF ONE OF US
SEES SOMETHING,

1066
01:24:10,961 --> 01:24:13,428
HE CAN POINT IT OUT
TO THE OTHER.

1067
01:24:13,470 --> 01:24:14,930
YEAH, THAT'S
WHAT WE'LL DO,

1068
01:24:14,972 --> 01:24:21,937
AND WE'LL DO IT
RIGHT NOW.

1069
01:24:21,972 --> 01:24:24,439
HE HAD TIME
TO MAKE HIS BED

1070
01:24:24,481 --> 01:24:26,441
BEFORE HE RAN
FOR HIS LIFE.

1071
01:24:26,483 --> 01:24:28,443
WE'VE GOT TO LEAVE.
HE'S HAD PLENTY--

1072
01:24:28,485 --> 01:24:30,946
I TOLD YOU THE BOY
HAD TO STAY ALIVE,

1073
01:24:30,981 --> 01:24:32,447
AND I TOLD YOU WHY.

1074
01:24:32,482 --> 01:24:33,949
NOW, WHERE IS HE?

1075
01:24:33,991 --> 01:24:35,951
WHAT DID YOU
DO WITH HIM?

1076
01:24:35,993 --> 01:24:41,957
YOU REALLY THINK I'D
DO SOMETHING TO HIM?

1077
01:24:41,992 --> 01:24:42,958
OH, COLLIE.

1078
01:24:42,993 --> 01:24:44,960
LET'S BE NICE, HUH?

1079
01:24:45,002 --> 01:24:48,463
LET'S--LET'S LIE
DOWN A WHILE, HUH?

1080
01:24:48,505 --> 01:24:52,468
LET'S--LET'S GET
ALL NICE AND CALM.

1081
01:24:52,503 --> 01:24:55,471
SHALL WE?

1082
01:24:55,512 --> 01:24:58,974
TRY SOMETHING LIKE THAT AGAIN
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

1083
01:24:59,016 --> 01:25:01,477
I'M WARNING YOU
I'LL KILL YOU FOR THAT.

1084
01:25:01,512 --> 01:25:55,030
MAYBE. NOW YOU'RE DOING
SOMETHING ELSE FAST AND NO MAYBE.

1085
01:25:55,072 --> 01:25:58,033
WELL, I GUESS
I SCREWED UP, HUH?

1086
01:25:58,075 --> 01:26:00,035
DIDN'T HIT HIM
HARD ENOUGH.

1087
01:26:00,070 --> 01:26:01,036
WHAT HAPPENED?

1088
01:26:01,071 --> 01:26:05,541
YOU JUST LEAVE HIM OUT THERE
HOPING HE'D BE FOUND?

1089
01:26:05,582 --> 01:26:07,543
DID I? YOU TELL ME.

1090
01:26:07,584 --> 01:26:13,048
GUESS YOU
PROBABLY DID.

1091
01:26:13,083 --> 01:26:14,550
YOU DO, HUH?

1092
01:26:14,591 --> 01:26:17,052
YOU'D ACTUALLY
GIVE ME A BREAK?

1093
01:26:17,094 --> 01:26:18,554
WELL, SHOVE IT,
BRIGHT BOY.

1094
01:26:18,595 --> 01:26:21,056
I HIT HIM
WITH A BIG ROCK

1095
01:26:21,091 --> 01:26:22,558
AND LEFT HIM TO DIE.

1096
01:26:22,593 --> 01:26:27,563
IF I'D HAD TIME,
I'D HAVE BEAT HIS BRAINS OUT.

1097
01:26:27,604 --> 01:26:28,564
BE QUIET.

1098
01:26:28,605 --> 01:26:30,566
YOU'RE
UPSETTING THE BOY.

1099
01:26:30,601 --> 01:26:32,067
WHY THE HELL
SHOULD I?

1100
01:26:32,102 --> 01:26:36,572
DIDN'T I TRY TO
KILL HIM, YOU SON OF A BITCH?

1101
01:26:36,613 --> 01:26:38,073
I TRIED TO KILL HIM!

1102
01:26:38,115 --> 01:26:39,575
I MEANT TO! I DID!

1103
01:26:39,610 --> 01:26:43,579
I DID! I--

1104
01:26:43,614 --> 01:26:48,584
MRS. ANDERSON...
ISN'T IT?

1105
01:26:48,625 --> 01:26:54,590
I'M DR. GOLDMAN.

1106
01:26:54,631 --> 01:26:58,594
WELL, HELLO, DOCTOR.

1107
01:26:58,635 --> 01:27:01,096
I JUST DROPPED IN
FOR A MOMENT.

1108
01:27:01,131 --> 01:27:02,598
I'M DUE
AT THE OFFICE,

1109
01:27:02,633 --> 01:27:06,101
BUT I HAPPENED TO BE
OUT THIS WAY, AND...

1110
01:27:06,143 --> 01:27:07,603
YOUR SON?

1111
01:27:07,644 --> 01:27:11,106
COLLIE DIDN'T TELL ME YOU
HAD ANY CHILDREN.

1112
01:27:11,141 --> 01:27:14,109
IT'S HER NEPHEW.
HE'S VISITING FOR A FEW DAYS.

1113
01:27:14,151 --> 01:27:15,611
I SEE.

1114
01:27:15,652 --> 01:27:17,613
FINE-LOOKING BOY.

1115
01:27:17,654 --> 01:27:27,122
A LITTLE UNDER
THE WEATHER, IS HE?

1116
01:27:27,164 --> 01:27:29,625
NOT FEELING TOO WELL,
HUH, SONNY?

1117
01:27:29,660 --> 01:27:31,126
NEVER MIND.

1118
01:27:31,161 --> 01:27:35,631
YOU DON'T
NEED TO TALK.

1119
01:27:35,672 --> 01:27:41,136
LET'S SEE IF I DON'T
HAVE SOMETHING TO, UM...

1120
01:27:41,171 --> 01:27:44,640
NO, I GUESS NOT.

1121
01:27:44,681 --> 01:27:48,143
I REMEMBER I WAS LOOKING
FOR SOME THIS MORNING

1122
01:27:48,185 --> 01:27:50,646
BEFORE I LEFT THE OFFICE.

1123
01:27:50,681 --> 01:27:55,150
HE COULD DO
WITH A B-12 SHOT.

1124
01:27:55,192 --> 01:27:58,153
YOU MIGHT MENTION THAT
TO HIS MOTHER.

1125
01:27:58,195 --> 01:28:00,155
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

1126
01:28:00,190 --> 01:28:01,657
THANKS, DOCTOR.

1127
01:28:01,692 --> 01:28:03,158
DON'T MENTION IT.

1128
01:28:03,193 --> 01:28:21,677
JUST SORRY I COULDN'T DO
SOMETHING FOR HIM.

1129
01:28:21,712 --> 01:28:26,181
HOW DID IT HAPPEN,
COLLIE?

1130
01:28:26,223 --> 01:28:33,689
HOW COULD YOU
HAVE DONE IT?

1131
01:28:33,730 --> 01:28:35,691
GET OUT OF THE WAY.

1132
01:28:35,732 --> 01:28:37,693
DO YOU HEAR ME, COLLIE?

1133
01:28:37,734 --> 01:28:44,700
STAND OUT OF THE WAY
AT ONCE.

1134
01:28:44,741 --> 01:28:47,202
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

1135
01:28:47,244 --> 01:28:49,705
SOMEONE DUPED YOU
INTO THIS.

1136
01:28:49,740 --> 01:28:54,209
THEY'RE USING YOU
FOR THEIR OWN CRIMINAL PURPOSES.

1137
01:28:54,251 --> 01:28:58,714
IT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY DIFFERENCE, DOC.

1138
01:28:58,755 --> 01:29:00,716
YOU'RE NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

1139
01:29:00,751 --> 01:29:05,220
WE'RE LEAVING,
AND YOU'RE GOING TO STAY.

1140
01:29:05,262 --> 01:29:08,223
CAN'T I APPEAL TO YOU,
MRS. ANDERSON?

1141
01:29:08,265 --> 01:29:10,726
CAN'T YOU MAKE HIM
UNDERSTAND?

1142
01:29:10,761 --> 01:29:12,227
FAY, WE'RE LEAVING.

1143
01:29:12,262 --> 01:29:14,730
GET TOGETHER ANYTHING
YOU WANT TO TAKE

1144
01:29:14,771 --> 01:29:28,744
AND GO OUT TO THE CAR.

1145
01:29:28,785 --> 01:29:30,245
WELL...

1146
01:29:30,280 --> 01:29:57,773
I SUPPOSE IF THAT'S
THE WAY IT HAS TO BE.

1147
01:29:57,815 --> 01:29:59,274
THERE'S SOMETHING
INSIDE EVERY MAN

1148
01:29:59,309 --> 01:30:00,776
THAT KEEPS HIM GOING

1149
01:30:00,811 --> 01:30:03,278
LONG AFTER HE HAS
ANY REASON TO.

1150
01:30:03,313 --> 01:30:05,280
FOR YEARS I KEPT GOING

1151
01:30:05,322 --> 01:30:06,782
WHEN GOING
DIDN'T MAKE SENSE,

1152
01:30:06,824 --> 01:30:09,785
AND NOW I JUST
HAD TO KEEP GOING.

1153
01:30:09,820 --> 01:31:21,815
I HAD TO HAVE
THE END COME.

1154
01:31:21,857 --> 01:31:23,317
SO, KID.

1155
01:31:23,358 --> 01:31:25,819
YOU SEE ANYTHING
I'VE OVERLOOKED?

1156
01:31:25,861 --> 01:31:29,323
IF YOU THINK OF ANYTHING,
JUST LET ME KNOW.

1157
01:31:29,364 --> 01:31:32,326
WE'RE NOT GOING
TO NEED ALL THIS.

1158
01:31:32,367 --> 01:31:35,329
I WANT YOU AND FAY
TO BE COMFORTABLE.

1159
01:31:35,370 --> 01:31:39,333
YOU MAY HAVE TO HOLE UP
HERE FOR QUITE A WHILE.

1160
01:31:39,374 --> 01:31:40,834
THERE'S PLENTY.

1161
01:31:40,876 --> 01:31:42,336
WHAT I MEAN IS,

1162
01:31:42,377 --> 01:31:44,838
YOU NEVER KNOW
WHEN YOU'LL NEED SOMETHING,

1163
01:31:44,880 --> 01:31:47,341
AND I WON'T BE
AROUND TO GET IT.

1164
01:31:47,382 --> 01:31:49,843
WELL, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT IT.

1165
01:31:49,885 --> 01:31:53,847
I BETTER GET INTO TOWN
AND CHECK ON THE COPS,

1166
01:31:53,889 --> 01:31:56,850
MAKE SURE THEY'RE NOT
COOKING ANYTHING UP.

1167
01:31:56,892 --> 01:31:59,853
STAY RIGHT
WHERE YOU ARE.

1168
01:31:59,895 --> 01:32:00,854
WE'RE GOING WITH YOU.

1169
01:32:00,896 --> 01:32:02,356
GOING WITH ME?

1170
01:32:02,397 --> 01:32:03,357
WHAT FOR?

1171
01:32:03,398 --> 01:32:05,859
FOR THE SAME REASON
YOU'RE GOING,

1172
01:32:05,901 --> 01:32:08,862
TO GET THE MONEY.

1173
01:32:08,904 --> 01:32:13,867
UH, IT AIN'T TIME, KID.

1174
01:32:13,909 --> 01:32:15,369
YOU KNOW IT AIN'T.

1175
01:32:15,410 --> 01:32:16,870
HOW DO I KNOW THAT?

1176
01:32:16,912 --> 01:32:19,373
YOU KNOW THAT
BECAUSE WE MADE A PLAN.

1177
01:32:19,414 --> 01:32:20,374
FORGET IT.

1178
01:32:20,415 --> 01:32:21,875
IT DOESN'T
CHANGE ANYTHING.

1179
01:32:21,917 --> 01:32:24,378
SEE, UH,
FAY DOESN'T TRUST ME,

1180
01:32:24,419 --> 01:32:26,380
AND I DON'T TRUST HER.

1181
01:32:26,421 --> 01:32:27,881
WE BOTH
DON'T TRUST YOU,

1182
01:32:27,923 --> 01:32:30,384
BUT I CAN
FIX THAT PART--YOU.

1183
01:32:30,425 --> 01:32:34,388
WE'LL PARK NEAR THE TERMINAL
WHERE I CAN SEE YOU.

1184
01:32:34,429 --> 01:32:35,889
YOU GOT 15 MINUTES.

1185
01:32:35,931 --> 01:32:38,392
YOU'RE NOT BACK,
I'LL TIP OFF THE COPS.

1186
01:32:38,433 --> 01:32:39,893
KID, I--

1187
01:32:39,935 --> 01:32:49,903
YES?

1188
01:32:49,945 --> 01:32:52,406
I'M GOING TO LEVEL
WITH YOU.

1189
01:32:52,447 --> 01:32:56,410
I'M NOT QUITE THE
GUY YOU THINK I AM.

1190
01:32:56,451 --> 01:32:57,911
SURE ABOUT THAT?

1191
01:32:57,953 --> 01:33:00,414
YEAH.

1192
01:33:00,455 --> 01:33:05,419
I'VE GOT NO PIPELINES
INTO THE DEPARTMENT.

1193
01:33:05,460 --> 01:33:06,920
THE GUYS I KNOW,

1194
01:33:06,962 --> 01:33:09,923
THEY WON'T EVEN
SPEAK TO ME ANYMORE.

1195
01:33:09,965 --> 01:33:12,926
THEY SEE ME COMING,
AND, UH...

1196
01:33:12,968 --> 01:33:15,429
THEY TURN
THE OTHER WAY.

1197
01:33:15,471 --> 01:33:17,931
YOU'RE NOT SURE
WHOEVER GETS THE MONEY

1198
01:33:17,973 --> 01:33:19,433
ISN'T WALKING
INTO A TRAP.

1199
01:33:19,475 --> 01:33:20,434
RIGHT.

1200
01:33:20,476 --> 01:33:22,436
YOU'RE GOING TO FIND OUT
AWFULLY FAST.

1201
01:33:22,478 --> 01:33:24,438
KID.

1202
01:33:24,480 --> 01:33:26,940
DON'T MAKE ME
DO THIS, KID.

1203
01:33:26,982 --> 01:33:29,943
PLEASE DON'T
MAKE ME DO THIS.

1204
01:33:29,985 --> 01:33:35,449
IF ONE OF THOSE GUYS
SHOULD CALL BERT,

1205
01:33:35,491 --> 01:33:38,702
HE COULD BE THERE
IN FIVE MINUTES.

1206
01:33:38,744 --> 01:33:41,955
WE SAT THERE FOR
ANOTHER HALF-HOUR OR SO,

1207
01:33:41,997 --> 01:33:44,458
AND HE WAS TALKING
EVERY MINUTE OF IT.

1208
01:33:44,500 --> 01:33:47,961
THE WORDS POURED
OUT OF HIS MOUTH,

1209
01:33:48,003 --> 01:33:49,463
AND THEY DIDN'T
MEAN A THING TO ME.

1210
01:33:49,505 --> 01:33:51,965
THEY WERE JUST
A LOT OF NOISES

1211
01:33:52,007 --> 01:33:53,967
COMING FROM
A SICKISH-LOOKING FACE.

1212
01:33:54,009 --> 01:33:57,471
WHAT OTHER PEOPLE SAID
HAD NEVER MEANT A THING TO HIM.

1213
01:33:57,513 --> 01:33:58,972
NOW IT WAS HIS TURN.

1214
01:33:59,014 --> 01:34:00,474
NOW HE WAS MEANINGLESS,

1215
01:34:00,516 --> 01:34:03,477
AND WHAT HE SAID
WAS MEANINGLESS.

1216
01:34:03,519 --> 01:34:07,439
I'M BEGGING YOU.

1217
01:34:07,474 --> 01:34:13,946
I'VE GOT A BAD
FEELING ABOUT THIS.

1218
01:34:13,981 --> 01:34:19,451
IF THE COPS
DON'T GET ME...

1219
01:34:19,493 --> 01:34:20,953
WELL...

1220
01:34:20,994 --> 01:34:21,954
SHUT UP!

1221
01:34:21,995 --> 01:34:23,956
GET UP AND START MOVING.

1222
01:34:23,991 --> 01:36:00,511
I AM SO SICK
OF LOOKING AT YOU.

1223
01:36:00,546 --> 01:36:03,472
HOW'S OUR BOY DOING?

1224
01:36:03,514 --> 01:36:14,483
OUR BOY IS SICK.

1225
01:36:14,525 --> 01:36:15,984
THE WHITE ZONE

1226
01:36:16,026 --> 01:36:26,495
IS FOR PASSENGER LOADING
AND UNLOADING ONLY.

1227
01:36:26,537 --> 01:36:30,999
COLLIE, WHAT ARE
THEY DOING, HUH?

1228
01:36:31,041 --> 01:36:33,001
WHAT ARE THEY DOING?

1229
01:36:33,043 --> 01:36:35,003
WELL, DO SOMETHING.

1230
01:36:35,045 --> 01:36:37,005
LET'S GO.
COME ON. LET'S--

1231
01:36:37,047 --> 01:36:38,549
COLLIE, I'M SCARED.

1232
01:36:38,584 --> 01:36:41,510
I'M SO SCARED.

1233
01:36:41,552 --> 01:36:43,512
HEY.

1234
01:36:43,554 --> 01:36:46,014
UH, SOMETHING
THE MATTER, OFFICER?

1235
01:36:46,056 --> 01:36:48,559
I'M SITTING HERE
WITH MY WIFE, AND, UH--

1236
01:36:48,594 --> 01:36:50,060
WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR?

1237
01:36:50,095 --> 01:36:51,520
MY FRIEND
JACK BILLINGSLEY.

1238
01:36:51,562 --> 01:36:54,022
HE'S COMING IN
FROM THE EAST.

1239
01:36:54,064 --> 01:36:56,525
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
THIS YOUR CAR?

1240
01:36:56,567 --> 01:36:59,570
LET ME SEE YOUR
REGISTRATION.

1241
01:36:59,605 --> 01:37:03,532
YOU'VE GOT THE REGISTRATION,
HAVEN'T YOU, HONEY?

1242
01:37:03,574 --> 01:37:05,033
HAVEN'T I SEEN
YOU BEFORE?

1243
01:37:05,075 --> 01:37:08,078
WHAT DID YOU SAY
YOUR NAME WAS?

1244
01:37:08,113 --> 01:37:09,079
COLLINS.

1245
01:37:09,114 --> 01:37:12,040
I'M WAITING FOR MY
FRIEND JACK BILLINGSLEY.

1246
01:37:12,082 --> 01:37:13,542
I'VE SEEN YOU.

1247
01:37:13,584 --> 01:37:15,544
YOU EVER BEEN
IN TROUBLE?

1248
01:37:15,586 --> 01:37:18,046
HOW YOU DOING ON
THAT REGISTRATION, MA'AM?

1249
01:37:18,088 --> 01:37:21,550
I THINK YOU HAVE ME MIXED UP
WITH SOMEBODY ELSE.

1250
01:37:21,592 --> 01:37:24,553
I'M, UH, RETIRED NOW,
BUT I USED TO--

1251
01:37:24,595 --> 01:37:26,555
I AIN'T GOT YOU
MIXED UP.

1252
01:37:26,597 --> 01:37:28,098
I SEEN YOU.

1253
01:37:28,133 --> 01:37:34,062
LET ME SEE YOUR
DRIVER'S LICENSE.

1254
01:37:34,104 --> 01:37:35,564
HOLD IT.

1255
01:37:35,606 --> 01:37:37,065
COLLINS.

1256
01:37:37,107 --> 01:37:38,609
KID COLLINS.

1257
01:37:38,644 --> 01:37:42,571
WHY, SURE. I WON
100 BUCKS ON YOU.

1258
01:37:42,613 --> 01:37:43,572
YOU'RE RETIRED
NOW, KID?

1259
01:37:43,614 --> 01:37:47,618
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO GIVE YOU A HARD TIME,

1260
01:37:47,653 --> 01:37:49,119
BUT WITH
THIS GOING ON.

1261
01:37:49,154 --> 01:37:51,580
WHATISGOING ON HERE,
SOME TROUBLE?

1262
01:37:51,622 --> 01:37:55,083
YOU SAID IT. YOU SHOULD COME GET
YOUR FRIEND LATER.

1263
01:37:55,125 --> 01:37:56,585
LET'S SEE.

1264
01:37:56,627 --> 01:37:58,086
YOU BACK IT ON UP.

1265
01:37:58,128 --> 01:38:00,130
I'LL WAVE
YOU THROUGH.

1266
01:38:00,165 --> 01:38:12,100
OK.

1267
01:38:12,142 --> 01:38:13,101
AAH!

1268
01:38:13,143 --> 01:38:14,603
HE'S GOT A GUN!

1269
01:38:14,645 --> 01:38:27,115
FREEZE!
DROP YOUR WEAPON!

1270
01:38:27,157 --> 01:38:29,159
YOU'D STILL BE
BETTER OFF

1271
01:38:29,194 --> 01:38:31,620
COMING BACK LATER
FOR YOUR FRIEND.

1272
01:38:31,662 --> 01:38:34,623
THIS PLACE IS GOING TO BE
A LITTLE CRAZY.

1273
01:38:34,665 --> 01:38:36,625
PULL IT ON OUT
THAT WAY.

1274
01:38:36,667 --> 01:38:39,670
I'LL SIGNAL FOR THE GUYS
TO LET YOU THROUGH.

1275
01:38:39,705 --> 01:39:27,718
THANK YOU.

1276
01:39:27,753 --> 01:39:29,219
[RADIO]
SO FAR THE KIDNAPPING

1277
01:39:29,254 --> 01:39:30,721
HAS STYMIED THE POLICE.

1278
01:39:30,756 --> 01:39:33,182
HOWEVER, THE AUTHORITIES
ARE OPTIMISTIC

1279
01:39:33,223 --> 01:39:34,516
BECAUSE MR. ROGERS,

1280
01:39:34,551 --> 01:39:36,018
THE VANDERVENTER FAMILY
CHAUFFEUR,

1281
01:39:36,053 --> 01:39:39,021
WAS ABLE TO TALK
WITH POLICE THIS AFTERNOON.

1282
01:39:39,062 --> 01:39:41,023
WHILE STILL
IN INTENSIVE CARE,

1283
01:39:41,064 --> 01:39:42,524
HE WAS ABLE TO PROVIDE

1284
01:39:42,559 --> 01:39:45,027
THE FIRST DETAILED
DESCRIPTION OF THE SUSPECT.

1285
01:39:45,062 --> 01:39:46,528
WAIT. THIS JUST IN.

1286
01:39:46,563 --> 01:39:49,531
THE POLICE ARE REPORTING
A SIGHTING OF THE SUSPECT

1287
01:39:49,573 --> 01:39:52,534
AS HE FLED THE SCENE
OF A SHOOTOUT

1288
01:39:52,569 --> 01:39:53,535
AT THE AIRPORT
MOMENTS AGO.

1289
01:39:53,570 --> 01:39:56,038
HE'S IDENTIFIED AS
KEVIN "KID" COLLINS,

1290
01:39:56,073 --> 01:39:59,541
AN EX-BOXER WHO RECENTLY
MOVED TO THE AREA.

1291
01:39:59,583 --> 01:40:02,044
HE WAS LAST SEEN TRAVELING
WITH A WOMAN

1292
01:40:02,085 --> 01:40:04,046
POLICE BELIEVE MAY HAVE
BEEN ABDUCTED

1293
01:40:04,081 --> 01:40:05,547
BY THE KIDNAPPERS.

1294
01:40:05,582 --> 01:40:08,050
IN WHAT MAY BE
A RELATED DEVELOPMENT,

1295
01:40:08,091 --> 01:40:10,052
THE BODY
OF LONGTIME RESIDENT

1296
01:40:10,093 --> 01:40:12,554
DR. JAKE GOLDMAN
WAS FOUND THIS MORNING

1297
01:40:12,589 --> 01:40:15,057
BOUND AND GAGGED
IN AN ISOLATED DESERT HOME.

1298
01:40:15,092 --> 01:40:17,559
THE 50-YEAR-OLD BACHELOR
APPARENTLY DIED

1299
01:40:17,594 --> 01:40:20,562
FROM A SINGLE BLOW
TO THE HEART.

1300
01:40:20,604 --> 01:40:34,576
THE VALLEY PLANNING
COMMISSION IS MEETING...

1301
01:40:34,611 --> 01:40:37,079
WHEN A MAN STOPS CARING
WHAT HAPPENS,

1302
01:40:37,114 --> 01:40:40,582
ALL THE STRAIN
IS LIFTED FROM HIM.

1303
01:40:40,624 --> 01:40:42,584
SUSPICION AND WORRY
AND FEAR,

1304
01:40:42,619 --> 01:40:47,089
ALL THE THINGS THAT TWIST
HIS THINKING OUT OF FOCUS,

1305
01:40:47,124 --> 01:40:48,090
ARE BRUSHED ASIDE,

1306
01:40:48,132 --> 01:40:50,092
AND HE CAN SEE PEOPLE

1307
01:40:50,134 --> 01:40:53,095
EXACTLY AS THEY ARE
AT LAST...

1308
01:40:53,130 --> 01:40:55,597
AS I SAW FAY THEN--

1309
01:40:55,632 --> 01:40:57,099
WEAK AND FRIGHTENED,

1310
01:40:57,134 --> 01:40:59,601
BUT BASICALLY AS GOOD
AS A PERSON COULD BE

1311
01:40:59,643 --> 01:41:03,605
AND HATING HERSELF
FOR NOT BEING BETTER.

1312
01:41:03,640 --> 01:41:06,108
SUDDENLY THE ONLY THING
THAT MATTERED

1313
01:41:06,143 --> 01:41:07,609
WAS THAT SHE LIVE.

1314
01:41:07,644 --> 01:41:10,112
IT WAS THE ONLY WAY
MY HAVING LIVED

1315
01:41:10,154 --> 01:41:11,613
COULD MAKE ANY SENSE.

1316
01:41:11,655 --> 01:41:15,117
IT WAS WHY I HAD BEEN
MADE LIKE I WAS--

1317
01:41:15,152 --> 01:41:16,618
TO DO SOMETHING FOR HER

1318
01:41:16,653 --> 01:41:18,620
SHE COULDN'T DO
FOR HERSELF,

1319
01:41:18,655 --> 01:41:22,124
THEN TO PROTECT HER
SO THAT SHE COULD GO ON--

1320
01:41:22,166 --> 01:41:25,127
SO THAT SHE WOULD HAVE
THE REASON FOR LIVING

1321
01:41:25,162 --> 01:41:58,118
THAT I'D NEVER HAD.

1322
01:41:58,153 --> 01:42:00,621
FUNNY HOW SOMETIMES
THINGS THAT AREN'T TRUE

1323
01:42:00,656 --> 01:42:04,583
ARE MORE TRUE
THAN THE TRUTH...

1324
01:42:04,625 --> 01:42:07,085
BECAUSE IN A WAY
FAY HAD BEEN ABDUCTED.

1325
01:42:07,127 --> 01:42:09,129
NONE OF THIS
WOULD'VE HAPPENED

1326
01:42:09,164 --> 01:42:11,089
IF I HADN'T COME ALONG.

1327
01:42:11,131 --> 01:42:12,591
AS SHE SAID,

1328
01:42:12,633 --> 01:42:15,093
THIS SCHEME HAD BEEN
COOKING A LONG TIME.

1329
01:42:15,135 --> 01:42:18,639
NOW WITHOUT ME, IT WOULD
JUST BOIL AWAY TO NOTHING.

1330
01:42:18,674 --> 01:42:21,099
SHE HAD SENT ME AWAY ONCE,

1331
01:42:21,141 --> 01:42:23,101
BUT I CAME BACK.

1332
01:42:23,143 --> 01:42:24,603
I HAD TO.

1333
01:42:24,645 --> 01:42:31,610
AND NOW FAY WAS THE ONE
PAYING THE PRICE.

1334
01:42:31,652 --> 01:42:34,613
I NEEDED A WAY.

1335
01:42:34,655 --> 01:42:37,616
ONE LAST PLAN TO MAKE
THE WHOLE THING RIGHT

1336
01:42:37,658 --> 01:43:22,661
AND LEAVE HER
IN THE CLEAR.

1337
01:43:22,703 --> 01:43:25,664
WE KNOW WHAT TO DO.
LET'S GET IT OVER WITH.

1338
01:43:25,706 --> 01:43:26,665
MIGHT AS WELL.

1339
01:43:26,707 --> 01:43:31,170
ONE LAST THING, COLLIE.

1340
01:43:31,211 --> 01:43:33,672
WE'VE DONE SOME PRETTY
INEXCUSABLE THINGS.

1341
01:43:33,714 --> 01:43:35,674
I KNOW YOU WEREN'T
RESPONSIBLE.

1342
01:43:35,716 --> 01:43:39,720
YOU THOUGHT YOU HAD TO
PROTECT THE BOY FROM ME.

1343
01:43:39,755 --> 01:43:41,680
WHATEVER I SAID,
I'M SORRY.

1344
01:43:41,722 --> 01:43:43,682
FORGET IT.
IT WAS MY FAULT.

1345
01:43:43,724 --> 01:43:46,685
I THOUGHT IT WAS SMART
TO KEEP THE BOY ALIVE.

1346
01:43:46,727 --> 01:43:50,731
NOW I SEE IT WAS
ABOUT THE DUMBEST THING I EVER DID.

1347
01:43:50,766 --> 01:43:53,192
WELL...

1348
01:43:53,233 --> 01:43:57,696
REGARDLESS WHO WAS
AT FAULT, I...

1349
01:43:57,738 --> 01:43:59,740
WHAT?

1350
01:43:59,775 --> 01:44:02,701
WHY, COLLIE,
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?

1351
01:44:02,743 --> 01:44:04,203
DON'T YOU GET IT?

1352
01:44:04,244 --> 01:44:05,704
YOU CALL ME STUPID,

1353
01:44:05,746 --> 01:44:07,706
AND YOU DON'T SEE
WHAT I MEAN?

1354
01:44:07,748 --> 01:44:09,249
NO, I DON'T SEE.

1355
01:44:09,284 --> 01:44:12,211
YOU'VE GOT TO.

1356
01:44:12,252 --> 01:44:14,213
UNCLE BUD
COULD BE BLAMED

1357
01:44:14,254 --> 01:44:16,215
FOR PRACTICALLY
EVERYTHING I'VE DONE,

1358
01:44:16,256 --> 01:44:17,216
COULDN'T HE?

1359
01:44:17,257 --> 01:44:18,258
AND YOU--

1360
01:44:18,293 --> 01:44:20,260
WHAT ARE YOU
GETTING AT?

1361
01:44:20,295 --> 01:44:22,221
YOU'VE GOT IT
JUST ABOUT PERFECT.

1362
01:44:22,262 --> 01:44:25,724
IT LOOKS ABOUT 100%
BETTER FOR YOU THAN FOR ME.

1363
01:44:25,766 --> 01:44:27,726
YOU'RE A WOMAN
LIVING ALONE.

1364
01:44:27,768 --> 01:44:29,269
UNCLE BUD
THREATENED YOU.

1365
01:44:29,304 --> 01:44:31,730
YOU WERE SCARED
TO DEATH OF ME,

1366
01:44:31,772 --> 01:44:33,732
SO YOU WENT ALONG
WITH THIS.

1367
01:44:33,774 --> 01:44:36,235
I ASKED YOU WHAT
YOU'RE GETTING AT.

1368
01:44:36,276 --> 01:44:39,279
YOU REALLY DON'T
GET IT, DO YOU?

1369
01:44:39,314 --> 01:44:42,241
THEN I GUESS
YOU WOULDN'T AT THAT.

1370
01:44:42,282 --> 01:44:45,244
IT WON'T HURT YOU
IF THE BOY TALKS,

1371
01:44:45,285 --> 01:44:48,247
BUT IT WILL
HURT ME PLENTY.

1372
01:44:48,288 --> 01:44:50,290
SO...

1373
01:44:50,325 --> 01:44:52,751
THERE'S YOUR ANSWER.

1374
01:44:52,793 --> 01:44:54,753
ALL SPELLED OUT FOR YOU.

1375
01:44:54,795 --> 01:45:06,765
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO DO ANY TALKING.

1376
01:45:06,807 --> 01:45:08,267
YOU DON'T MEAN THAT.

1377
01:45:08,308 --> 01:45:09,810
YOU CAN'T MEAN IT.

1378
01:45:09,845 --> 01:45:13,772
YOU'VE HAD EVEN MORE
THAN A NORMAL PERSON COULD TAKE,

1379
01:45:13,814 --> 01:45:15,774
AND YOU'RE EXCITED
AND FRIGHTENED.

1380
01:45:15,816 --> 01:45:18,318
YOU DON'T MEAN IT,
DO YOU, DARLING?

1381
01:45:18,353 --> 01:45:19,820
I KNOW MY COLLIE.

1382
01:45:19,855 --> 01:45:21,280
OOH.

1383
01:45:21,321 --> 01:45:24,283
I REALLY HAD YOU FOOLED,
DIDN'T I?

1384
01:45:24,324 --> 01:45:26,285
WELL, I GUESS I SHOULD.

1385
01:45:26,326 --> 01:45:27,786
ALL THIS PRACTICE.

1386
01:45:27,828 --> 01:45:29,830
I WAS UP FOR MURDER.

1387
01:45:29,865 --> 01:45:32,791
IT WAS THE ONLY THING
I COULD THINK OF,

1388
01:45:32,833 --> 01:45:34,793
SO I WENT INTO THE ACT,

1389
01:45:34,835 --> 01:45:36,295
AND IT GOT ME OFF.

1390
01:45:36,336 --> 01:45:38,839
IT LOOKED LIKE
SUCH A GOOD DEAL,

1391
01:45:38,874 --> 01:45:40,799
I STARTED WORKING IT
FULL-TIME.

1392
01:45:40,841 --> 01:45:42,301
WHAT ACT?

1393
01:45:42,342 --> 01:45:44,803
THE CRAZY STUFF, FAY.

1394
01:45:44,845 --> 01:45:47,306
HELL, IT'S BETTER
THAN A PENSION.

1395
01:45:47,347 --> 01:45:50,809
I CAN JUST ROAM AROUND,
DOING WHATEVER I WANT,

1396
01:45:50,851 --> 01:45:52,811
ACTING STUPID.

1397
01:45:52,853 --> 01:45:54,813
WHEN I GET
A LITTLE TIRED,

1398
01:45:54,855 --> 01:45:58,358
I JUST CHECK INTO AN
INSTITUTION FOR A WHILE.

1399
01:45:58,393 --> 01:45:59,359
HELL, I TELL YOU,

1400
01:45:59,394 --> 01:46:02,321
SOMETIMES THEY GIVE YOU
A PRIVATE ROOM,

1401
01:46:02,362 --> 01:46:04,323
ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO EAT.

1402
01:46:04,364 --> 01:46:06,825
I DON'T KNOW WHY
PEOPLE DON'T GET WISE.

1403
01:46:06,867 --> 01:46:09,369
YOU DO ALL SORTS
OF THINGS

1404
01:46:09,404 --> 01:46:10,829
TO GIVE YOURSELF AWAY,

1405
01:46:10,871 --> 01:46:11,830
BUT SOMEHOW,

1406
01:46:11,872 --> 01:46:13,832
THEY NEVER CATCH ON.

1407
01:46:13,874 --> 01:46:17,336
THEY KEEP FALLING
FOR THE SAME ACT

1408
01:46:17,377 --> 01:46:19,880
AND FEELING SORRY
FOR YOU.

1409
01:46:19,915 --> 01:46:20,839
GOD.

1410
01:46:20,881 --> 01:46:25,844
LET'S JUST GET THIS
OVER WITH.

1411
01:46:25,886 --> 01:46:27,346
I WON'T KILL YOU.

1412
01:46:27,387 --> 01:46:28,847
I'LL JUST MESS YOU UP,

1413
01:46:28,889 --> 01:46:31,350
MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
THERE WAS A STRUGGLE.

1414
01:46:31,391 --> 01:46:33,852
I TRIED TO KEEP YOU
FROM KILLING THE BOY.

1415
01:46:33,894 --> 01:46:35,854
THE GUN ACCIDENTALLY
WENT OFF.

1416
01:46:35,896 --> 01:46:38,899
DO ANYTHING TO ME,
BUT DON'T KILL HIM.

1417
01:46:38,934 --> 01:46:40,400
THERE'S AN IDEA.

1418
01:46:40,435 --> 01:46:48,867
INSTEAD OF BUMPING OFF THE BRAT
AND LEAVING HIM ALONE.

1419
01:46:48,909 --> 01:46:50,410
I LIKE YOU, CHARLIE.

1420
01:46:50,445 --> 01:46:52,371
I LIKE YOU VERY MUCH.

1421
01:46:52,412 --> 01:47:09,429
[GUNSHOT]

1422
01:47:09,464 --> 01:47:11,890
IT'S OK, FAY.

1423
01:47:11,932 --> 01:47:31,910
YOU DID
THE RIGHT THING.

1424
01:47:31,952 --> 01:47:34,413
YOU AND ME
TOGETHER FOREVER.

1425
01:47:34,454 --> 01:47:36,415
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
THAT, COLLIE?

1426
01:47:36,457 --> 01:47:41,920
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
THERE COULD BE A YOU AND ME?

1427
01:47:41,962 --> 01:47:43,922
I KNOW IT, FAY.

